---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SkillTags from '../components/SkillTags.astro';
import site from '../data/site.json';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="I'm a problem-solving Flutter developer in Bristol — messy repos, AI clean-up, and full-stack builds.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-10 items-start">
      <img
        src={site.photo}
        alt={`Portrait of ${site.name}`}
        width="192"
        height="192"
        class="w-48 h-48 rounded-2xl object-cover object-top shadow-lg shrink-0"
        onerror="this.src='/images/placeholder-avatar.svg'"
      />
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-ink">About</h1>
        <p class="mt-2 text-ink-muted">{site.title} · {site.location}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 prose">
      <p>
        I'm a senior Flutter developer who specialises in solving problems — the kind other teams
        inherit and struggle with. Messy repos with no clear architecture. AI-generated code that
        looks fine until it hits production. Half-finished prototypes that need someone to take them
        start to finish. I come in, figure out what's actually broken, and ship working software.
      </p>
      <p>
        That approach is how I built <strong>Melody</strong> from zero: co-founder and sole mobile
        developer of a women's health platform with an AI-powered Menstrual Coach. Full-stack
        delivery — Melos monorepo, Vertex AI with RAG and function calling, 14+ tracking dimensions,
        RevenueCat freemium monetisation, 250+ tests (unit through Patrol E2E), and automated
        Fastlane delivery to the App Store and Play Store.
      </p>
      <p>
        Before Melody I led a greenfield rewrite at HomeLink and spent two and a half years on
        Nextbase's flagship iQ dash cam app as part of a 10-person Flutter team. Strong
        communication comes from a prior career in mathematics teaching — I explain trade-offs
        clearly to technical and non-technical stakeholders alike. Outside client work I've shipped
        8+ independent apps, mentor aspiring developers, and founded
        <strong>Flutter SouthWest</strong>, Bristol's Flutter meetup (supported by Women's Tech Hub).
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mb-6">Community & leadership</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4">
        {
          site.community.map((item) => (
            <li class="rounded-xl border border-border p-5">
              <p class="font-semibold text-ink">{item.role}</p>
              <p class="text-brand-600 font-medium">{item.organisation}</p>
              {item.description && <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-muted">{item.description}</p>}
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mb-6">Education</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        {
          site.education.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex gap-4 text-sm">
              <span class="font-medium text-ink-muted w-12 shrink-0">{item.year}</span>
              <div>
                <p class="font-medium text-ink">{item.qualification}</p>
                {item.institution && <p class="text-ink-muted">{item.institution}</p>}
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-14">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-ink mb-6">Languages</h2>
      <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {
          site.languages.map((language) => (
            <li class="rounded-full bg-brand-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-brand-700 border border-brand-100">
              {language}
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-14">
      <SkillTags skills={site.skills} />
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
